00:43:58.080 --> 00:44:10.479
Okay, just to start wrapping things up, you can also disable brand.yaml.

00:44:10.479 --> 00:44:15.760
Like, let's say there is a document in your project that you don't want to have brand.yaml.

00:44:16.399 --> 00:44:18.320
You can specify brand is false.

00:44:22.639 --> 00:44:26.800
Another thing, especially if you're coming from a previous version of Cordo and you're

00:44:26.800 --> 00:44:30.000
like, oh, how do all these things work together?

00:44:30.000 --> 00:44:36.639
So the brand.yaml file will always take the lowest priority in the styles, and the find

00:44:36.639 --> 00:44:39.600
themes will override the brand settings.

00:44:40.239 --> 00:44:48.159
So, for example, here, if you have these themes listed in your Cordo.yaml project file,

00:44:50.479 --> 00:44:55.600
your brand.yaml will be overridden by Cosmo or by Tweaks.sas.

00:44:55.600 --> 00:45:02.000
So while it could be useful in some cases, you may want the brand settings to take priority,

00:45:02.879 --> 00:45:05.840
in which case you would want to switch to order.

00:45:05.840 --> 00:45:11.919
So it's just something you have to be aware of in case you have more than one file that

00:45:11.919 --> 00:45:16.000
your Cordo project or documents are referencing.

00:45:16.000 --> 00:45:27.439
And in terms of how to share brand.yaml, there are a couple of ideas that we have,

00:45:27.439 --> 00:45:33.120
but we also would love to hear about how you work with brand.yaml and what would work for

00:45:33.120 --> 00:45:33.840
you.

00:45:33.840 --> 00:45:40.719
But two ideas if you want to share your brand.yaml file, say, with your colleagues or your teammate

00:45:40.719 --> 00:45:41.679
or anything like that.

00:45:42.239 --> 00:45:48.560
With Cordo, you can create an extension, and if somebody has built an extension similar

00:45:48.560 --> 00:45:54.000
to how in this presentation, for example, I installed the Font Awesome extension.

00:45:54.719 --> 00:45:58.719
So in the terminal, I say Cordo add and the name of the extension.

00:45:59.439 --> 00:46:02.639
Other people can do that as long as you've created an extension, too.

00:46:02.639 --> 00:46:06.239
So it can work for Cordo projects and things like that.

00:46:07.199 --> 00:46:14.399
A more straightforward way is upload it to a GitHub repo or some sort of common place

00:46:14.399 --> 00:46:20.159
where it can be downloaded and try to maintain a single source of truth in terms of

00:46:22.879 --> 00:46:24.800
sharing your brand.yaml file.

00:46:24.800 --> 00:46:30.239
But again, we're welcome to suggestions and hearing about what works and doesn't work

00:46:30.239 --> 00:46:35.760
in terms of this idea of sharing brand.yaml files across an organization.

00:46:36.800 --> 00:46:43.679
But just to sum up, you want to ensure your work consistently follows brand guidelines

00:46:43.679 --> 00:46:44.879
and avoid duplication.

00:46:45.520 --> 00:46:51.360
And you can share a single brand.yaml file across your organizations so that everybody

00:46:51.360 --> 00:46:56.080
has these easily applicable branding guidelines.

00:46:56.639 --> 00:47:02.560
You eliminate the need for every single person to recreate their design for each project.

00:47:03.120 --> 00:47:08.959
And you can create custom themes for whatever project it is that you're creating.

00:47:08.959 --> 00:47:14.800
And so if you are thinking about all of those things, brand.yaml might be the tool for you.

00:47:17.919 --> 00:47:25.439
And in terms of the future of brand.yaml, for us, our users, the team is actively working

00:47:25.439 --> 00:47:30.159
on extending brand.yaml to plots and tables.

00:47:30.159 --> 00:47:37.520
And so if you are a Python user, there is already a way of doing that using a Python

00:47:37.520 --> 00:47:41.040
package, as you can see in this example here.

00:47:41.040 --> 00:47:43.600
And so coming soon for us, our users.

00:47:43.600 --> 00:47:51.840
And you can keep an eye out on the Pozit blog or the Shiny blog for more information.

00:47:52.800 --> 00:48:00.000
And then also additional tools for creating your brand.yaml file using LLMs.

00:48:00.719 --> 00:48:05.600
But that being said, brand.yaml is a very new project.

00:48:05.600 --> 00:48:09.520
And we'd absolutely love your feedback to help shape its future.

00:48:10.159 --> 00:48:13.439
And so things might change as we learn what works and what doesn't.

00:48:13.439 --> 00:48:17.840
And if you want to be part of that, please join the discussion on GitHub.

