00:54:23.439 --> 00:54:24.639
They really do want to hear.

00:54:24.639 --> 00:54:29.040
And so I think if they hear there is a lot of type support

00:54:29.040 --> 00:54:33.600
that now that the documents and reports and things like that

00:54:33.600 --> 00:54:34.800
are kind of fleshed out,

00:54:34.800 --> 00:54:38.320
that they would be able to dedicate more effort on it.

00:54:38.320 --> 00:54:39.679
So please do reach out.

00:54:41.439 --> 00:54:44.239
I think this came in from someone that came in later,

00:54:44.239 --> 00:54:49.919
but just to be clear, brand YAML can be used in PDF with types,

00:54:49.919 --> 00:54:52.320
but support is a development, right?

00:54:53.600 --> 00:54:54.399
Yes, that's right.

00:54:57.280 --> 00:55:02.479
Generally, when you're trying to get the latest versions

00:55:02.479 --> 00:55:03.760
of different things,

00:55:05.040 --> 00:55:07.760
I have noticed that the latest version of Quarto

00:55:07.760 --> 00:55:10.719
is sometimes newer than the version built in with RStudio.

00:55:10.719 --> 00:55:13.120
Can I use the latest version of Quarto

00:55:13.120 --> 00:55:16.239
with the current version of RStudio?

00:55:18.080 --> 00:55:22.080
Yes, I don't remember what was the first version

00:55:22.879 --> 00:55:24.639
of RStudio that shipped with Quarto,

00:55:24.639 --> 00:55:28.399
but yes, even if you don't have the latest RStudio,

00:55:28.399 --> 00:55:32.000
you can use the latest Quarto and vice versa.

00:55:32.800 --> 00:55:36.719
One tool that I've been playing around with is called QVM.

00:55:38.159 --> 00:55:40.159
Mm-hmm.

00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:48.639
For managing your different Quarto installations,

00:55:49.199 --> 00:55:53.840
and it has a handy QVM install latest or something like that,

00:55:53.840 --> 00:55:57.120
and then you can also change what version you're using,

00:55:57.120 --> 00:55:59.439
if you need to go back for whatever reason.

00:55:59.439 --> 00:56:00.959
But just to answer the question,

00:56:00.959 --> 00:56:03.439
yeah, you don't have to be in the latest and greatest

00:56:03.439 --> 00:56:06.719
of everything in order to use it.

00:56:06.719 --> 00:56:12.080
But for brand YAML, you do need version 1.6 or above of Quarto.

